visuals.description:
polySin()/polyCos() & infSin()/infCos() are 4 little helper functions I wrote for Processing. The former are mapping the sin/cos wave onto an N-edged convex polygon, the latter do the same with the infinity symbol.
Probably useful for loading animations.

float x = polySin(angle, edges);
float y = polyCos(angle, edges);

float x = infSin(angle);
float y = infCos(angle);

Controls:
- MOUSECLICK = change function

